Since the early 19th Century, it has been the custom of the Hine family to set aside the best Cognac produced during a particularly outstanding year for their own use, ultimately to be served to honored guests. Only recently, and for the first time, Francois Hine, the managing director of this venerable firm, has consented to part with a few of these treasured bottles—each is numbered and bears a back label relating the unique history of the contents, hand signed by a director. Normally $24.95. Quantity limited
